{
  "name": "stratus-fault-tolerant-revolution-ad-198-797e0e",
  "title": "The Fault Tolerant Revolution \u2014 Stratus/32 launch advertisement",
  "description": "Full-page Computerworld launch advertisement for the Stratus/32 Continuous Processing system circa mid-1981 \u2014 the advertising debut of Stratus Computer's hardware-based approach to fault tolerance. The ad contrasts Stratus's duplicate-hardware, tightly-coupled lockstep design with Tandem's software-checkpoint approach, claims price/performance competitive with non-fault-tolerant systems, and quotes a fully-duplexed configuration at under $130,000 including software. Artifact from Kastner's Stratus marketing tenure; documents the company's first broad-market positioning statement.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-04-25",
